    {"id": 14, "unit": "Unit 1", "unitName": "Foundations of American Democracy", "concept": "Enumerated Powers", "question": "Which is an enumerated power of Congress?", "options": ["Establishing local police departments", "Setting speed limits on highways", "Issuing driver's licenses", "Regulating interstate commerce"], "answer": "D", "explanation": "The power to regulate interstate commerce is explicitly listed in Article I, Section 8."},
